annotationA: Probable arginine--tRNA ligase, cytoplasmic; Forms part of a macromolecular complex that catalyzes the attachment of specific amino acids to cognate tRNAs during protein synthesis
annotationB: Methionine--tRNA ligase, mitochondrial; ATP binding; methionine-tRNA ligase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: methionyl-tRNA aminoacylation; Belongs to the class-I aminoacyl-tRNA synthetase family
